sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_I766222
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Encodes for the Human MTMR1 phosphatase fused to an EE zipper under the control of pSte5, a weak constitutive promoter
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Nili Sommovilla
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: composite part. see individual parts for each source
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: for more info into cloning strategy, see the UCSF iGEM 2007 wiki

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_I766557
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: low expression, constitutive promoter in yeast
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Nili Sommovilla

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_I766215
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Start Codon + Xho site + Combinatorial Cloning A site
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Nili Sommovilla

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_I766216
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Adaptor Region for "B" Site in Combinatorial Cloning Approach
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Nili Sommovilla

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_I766102
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: binds with the complementary zipper, RR. Can be used to create binding interactions between desired elements through fusing the zipper pair to the appropriate genes.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Nili Sommovilla
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: not a standard biobrick. cloned using primers containing an adaptor region for combinatorial cloning using type IIs restriction enzymes.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_I766217
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Adaptor used for non-pSte2 constructs; contains a stop codon, a BamHI site followed by the combinatorial D adaptor region, followed by Adh terminator
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Nili Sommovilla
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Adh terminator derived from genomic sequence; other components are synthetic.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: for more information on combinatorial cloning, see documentation on the 2007 UCSF iGEM wiki
